ls said two <LOCATION> Vietnamese </LOCATION> women were raped and dumped on a remote Thai island before arriving at the camp. The women reported that 26 people in their boat were killed by Thai pirates late last year. The officials said such attacks by Thai pirates had decreased since the early 1980s when Thai and <LOCATION> Malaysian </LOCATION> authorities had stepped up boat patrols. The government reported that in March, about 2,000 Vietnamese refugees landed on <LOCATION> Malaysian </LOCATION> shores, almost double the average for the past few months. There are now about 16,500 Vienamese boat people in <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Malaysia </LOCATION> and the nations of the region accept the refugees only for temporary stay pending permanent settlement in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION>.
