f restoring the <LOCATION> Alamo </LOCATION> and telling the history of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> accurately. `` They are blood descendants of the heroes of the <LOCATION> Alamo </LOCATION>,'' <PERSON> Cisneros </PERSON> said. `` No one else will treat either the building or the history of the period with the care and reverence they bring to the task.'' <PERSON> Garcia </PERSON>, who had asked the Daughters to open their records, agrees they take care of the <LOCATION> Alamo </LOCATION> as no one else could and adds, `` the state is not in a position to be assuming new burdens.'' <PERSON> Pauline </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON>, president of the Daughters' Alamo chapter, said hard work went into making the <LOCATION> Alamo </LOCATION> the tourist attraction it is today. `` The older members brought in their husbands, their kids, even their maids to clean the place out,'' she said. `` Where were all these people when we were having such a hard time with it?''
