overnor in 1986. But in November 1985 he dropped those plans, saying the criticism and publicity surrounding the harassment case were unbearable. He also said he regretted having settled the `` unfounded and ridiculous'' lawsuit. By filing the Chapter 7 bankruptcy petition Friday, <PERSON> Stephan </PERSON> stops the garnishment, starting with his next paycheck. In the petition, <PERSON> Stephan </PERSON> listed his debts as unknown, and gave his assets at $ 70,401, all of which he said are protected from creditors under Chapter 7. Despite his financial troubles, <PERSON> Stephan </PERSON> said, `` I am proud of my record as attorney general and will continue to carry out my duties to the very best of my ability.'' <PERSON> Stephan </PERSON> is serving his third four-year term as attorney general. He has not indicated whether he intends to seek a fourth term next year.
