</LOCATION> state and northern <LOCATION> Oregon </LOCATION>. Another cold front moving across <LOCATION> Southern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> brought gusty winds to the <LOCATION> Mojave </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Desert </LOCATION>. Temperatures around the nation at 2 p.m. EST ranged from 29 degrees at Caribou and Limestone, <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Saranac </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, to 89 degrees at Thermal, <LOCATION> Calif </LOCATION>. The low in the nation Saturday morning was 8 degrees at <LOCATION> Marquette </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> forecast for Sunday called for scattered rainshowers from western <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION> across much of the middle <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, southern portions of the upper <LOCATION> Great </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lakes </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> to the central Appalachians; rain falling across much of the northern and central <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> and the northern and central Intermountain region; and strong, gusty winds across the northern and central Rockies. High temperatures were expected to be in the 30s over <LOCATION> northeast </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION>, northwest <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>, western upper <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> and northern <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION>; in the 40s and 50s from the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Northwest </LOCATION> across the northern and central Rockies, <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dakota </LOCATION>, much of the upper <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> and the Great Lakes to the northern <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>; the 80s 